g zone): flag and investigate root cause\n- CPQL \u003e $160 (pause zone): audit immediately, recommend pause via #approvals\n\nSEED AUDIENCE REBUILD (when recommending audience change):\n- Use HubSpot deal/lead association filters: Closed Won or Qualified stage deals only\n- NEVER reference contact-level product interest properties - they have 0% fill rate and are empty\n- Audience pauses require performance-lead approval via #approvals before execution\n\nCRO HANDOFF CHAIN (when CPQL traced to LP quality issue):\n- CRO Specialist ? UI/UX Designer ? Developer ? pixel verification ? LP sign-off\n- Pixel verification: BOTH Meta pixels must be observed firing on form submit\n- UTM passthrough: confirmed on hidden form fields before sign-off\n- LP sign-off only after both pixel firing AND UTM passthrough are confirmed\n\nKEYWORD CLEANUP (after pausing free/discount copy creatives):\n- Run keyword audit for matching search terms: ?????, ?????, ??????, free, discount\n- Add as ALWAYS_NEGATIVE in BOTH Arabic AND English - bilingual mandatory\n- Both scripts (Arabic + Latin) must be checked and negated\n\nAPPROVAL RULE (non-negotiable):\n- ALL budget cuts, campaign pauses, and audience changes must go to #approvals channel first\n- Wait for user ? reaction before any execution - ? skips\n- This sub-flow outputs RECOMMENDATIONS ONLY - it never auto-executes pauses or budget changes\n\nOutput valid JSON only:\n{\"root_cause\":string,\"zone\":string,\"worst_campaigns\":[{\"campaign_name\":string,\"cpql\":number,\"leads_qualified\":number,\"data_window_days\":number,\"recommendation\":string}],\"channel_recommendation\":string,\"requires_approval\":true,\"asana_title\":string}`;\n\nreturn [{json:{\n  system: systemPrompt,\n  messages:[{role:\u0027user\u0027,content:`Channel: ${ch}\\nCurrent CPQL: $${cpql} (${zoneLabel})\\n\\nCampaign breakdown (last 30 days, HubSpot CTE-joined):\\n${JSON.stringify(worst,null,2)}`}]\n}}];"
